HEADWORD: Birt
<hw>Birt</hw> <pr>(b⟦etil⟧rt)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>byrte</ets>; cf. F. <ets>bertonneau</ets>. Cf. <er>Bret</er>,
<er>Burt</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A fish of the turbot kind;
the brill.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>burt</asp>, <asp>bret</asp>,
or <asp>brut</asp>.]</altsp> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
